snippet.textDisplay:
despite what a lot of online discourse might say, i think in the last 2-3 years we've been seeing a renaissance era of gaming emerge and clair obscur really solidified that for me. it's really easy to see the cashgrab games riddled with microtransactions and feel angry about the greed of big gaming companies, but at the same time we're also seeing big games and small games alike, from medium and small-sized studios, blow expectations out of the water. 

idk if it was the inspiring success of a one-man passion project in stardew valley that kinda took us here, or the niche-to-mainstream trajectory of fromsoftware's titles, or consumer and developers mutual frustrations with corporate greed, or the pandemic giving people motivation to pursue their passion projects or, most likely, a combination of all these things. but whatever it was, it's fuckin incredible to see games like clair obscur prove the worth of video games as a medium for art and story. 

i could ramble forever about it i just love games so much and i love THIS GAME so much, and we all know that it's going to have an incredible legacy. we're definitely in one of the best eras for RPGs right now.
